/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:674:**Independence rule:** Two tasks are independent when neither appears in the other's transitive `**Prior:**` chain. The engine must not spawn two agents that could produce conflicting edits to the same task file. For directory workspaces, each task lives in a separate file, so file conflicts are avoided by construction.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:676:**Single-file plans:** Parallel mode is limited to `--parallel 1` for single-file plans because agents could produce conflicting edits to the same file. `rhei run` prints a warning if `--parallel` > 1 is requested with a single-file plan and falls back to sequential execution.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:680:Agents and callbacks are complementary, not exclusive:
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:682:- **Agent** does the work of the current state (coding, reviewing, fixing, writing artifacts).
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:683:- **`rhei run`** evaluates success or failure and performs the state transition.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:684:- **Callbacks** handle side effects of that transition (creating artifacts, spawning tasks, notifying systems).
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:686:When `rhei run` is in agent mode:
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:687:1. The agent is spawned for the current state.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:688:2. The agent performs work and exits.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:689:3. `rhei run` selects and executes the transition.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:690:4. `on_leave` / `on_enter` callbacks fire as part of that engine-driven transition.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:692:`--no-callbacks` suppresses callbacks but not agent or program spawning. `--no-agent` suppresses agent spawning but not program spawning or callbacks. `--no-program` suppresses program spawning but not agent spawning or callbacks. All three can be combined independently.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:696:When a task reaches a gating state (`gating: true`), `rhei run` does not spawn an agent. Instead it logs:
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:702:The task is skipped and the engine continues with other claimable tasks. When the human transitions the task out of the gating state (via `rhei transition`), the next run pass picks it up.
