/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:824:When an agent process exceeds its timeout:
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:826:1. `rhei run` sends `SIGTERM` to the agent process.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:828:3. Log to the task log: `agent timed out after {duration}`.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:829:4. Look for a timeout transition from the current state in the state machine.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:830:5. If a timeout transition exists, fire it (with its `on_leave`/`on_enter` callbacks).
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:831:6. If no timeout transition exists, the task remains in its current state and the engine logs a warning.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:835:Timeout transitions are declared in the `transitions` array with the `timeout` field. The existing `timeout` field in the transition schema (see [Transitions Specification](rhei-transitions.spec.md#transition-definition)) is used by `rhei run` to determine what to do when an agent times out.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:837:When a task is being worked by an agent and the agent exceeds the state's timeout:
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:839:1. The engine kills the agent process.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:840:2. The engine evaluates timeout transitions from the current state.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:841:3. The first matching timeout transition fires.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:850:    description: Task is ready for implementation.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:852:    agent_timeout: 30m
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:858:      The agent timed out while working on this task. A human must decide:
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:861:      - Increase the timeout and retry
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:867:    timeout: 30m
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:868:    on_enter: "cli:bash ./workflow.sh notify-timeout"
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:876:    description: Human decided to abandon after timeout
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:879:The `timeout` field on the transition and `agent_timeout` on the state serve different roles:
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:883:| `agent_timeout` | State definition | How long the engine waits before killing the agent process |
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:884:| `timeout` | Transition definition | Which transition fires when a timeout occurs (existing field, now also used by agent mode) |
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:886:When `agent_timeout` is set on a state but no transition with `timeout` exists from that state, the agent is killed but the task remains in its current state with a warning logged.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:890:Timeout transitions support the same `on_leave` and `on_enter` callbacks as any other transition. This enables notification, logging, or cleanup on timeout:
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:897:    timeout: 30m
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:899:    on_enter: "cli:bash ./workflow.sh notify-timeout"
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:902:The callback receives a `TransitionContext` with `triggeredBy: 'system'` and the timeout duration in `transitionData.timeout`.
/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:906:All agent stdout and stderr are captured to log files in the `runtime/logs/` directory relative to the workspace or plan root.
