/home/vjovanov/c/rhei/docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:978:When `--no-agent` is passed, `rhei run` reverts to pre-agent behavior: it advances tasks through the state machine using transition callbacks only, without spawning any agent processes. This is the existing behavior for backward compatibility.
