   906	All agent stdout and stderr are captured to log files in the `runtime/logs/` directory relative to the workspace or plan root.
   907	
   908	### Log File Naming
   909	
   910	| Scenario | Log file path |
   911	|----------|---------------|
   912	| Simple state | `runtime/logs/task-{task_id}-{state}.log` |
   913	| Counted-loop state | `runtime/logs/task-{task_id}-{state}-{visit_count}.log` |
   914	| Model-specific state | `runtime/logs/task-{task_id}-{state}-{model}.log` |
   915	| Both visits and model | `runtime/logs/task-{task_id}-{state}-{model}-{visit_count}.log` |
   916	
   917	### Log Format
   918	
   919	Each log file contains:
   920	
   921	```
   922	=== rhei agent log v1 ===
   923	agent: claude-code
   924	model: impl-fast
   925	provider: anthropic
   926	model_name: claude-sonnet-4-6
   927	task: 3
   928	state: pending
   929	started: 2026-04-20T10:30:00Z
   930	timeout: 30m
   931	plan: /home/user/project/plan.rhei.md
   932	mcp_servers: postgres,grafana?
   933	skills: test-authoring
   934	===
   935	
   936	<raw agent stdout and stderr, interleaved>
   937	
   938	=== exit ===
   939	code: 0
   940	duration: 4m23s
   941	ended: 2026-04-20T10:34:23Z
   942	===
   943	```
   944	
   945	The header and footer are added by `rhei run`. The `v1` suffix is the log format version — increment it when the header/footer structure changes. The body is the raw, unmodified output of the agent process.
   946	
   947	Each entry in `mcp_servers:` and `skills:` is the resolved id; an entry
   948	suffixed with `?` was declared `optional: true` and failed its availability
   949	check — it was dropped before spawn and is recorded for diagnostics. A
   950	missing line means the state declared no entries of that kind.
   951	
   952	### Log Directory
   953	
   954	`runtime/logs/` is created automatically by `rhei run` if it does not exist. `rhei reset` removes the entire `runtime/` directory, including logs.
